TITLE: Making API Requests to Electric Cloud Using Shell
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to make an API request to Electric Cloud using curl. It sets environment variables for the source ID, secret, and shape definition, then constructs a curl command to request a shape from the API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/electric-sql/electric/blob/main/website/product/cloud.md#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
export SOURCE_ID="8ea4e5fb-9217-4ca6-80b7-0a97581c4c10"
export SECRET="<long secret value>"

export SHAPE_DEFINITION="table=items&offset=-1"

curl -i "https://api.electric-sql.cloud/v1/shape?$SHAPE_DEFINITION\
    &source_id=$SOURCE_ID\
    &source_secret=$SECRET"
```

