TITLE: Traditional React Data Fetching Example
DESCRIPTION: Example showing traditional data fetching approach using React useState and useEffect hooks to fetch data from an API endpoint
SOURCE: https://github.com/electric-sql/electric/blob/main/website/blog/posts/2024-12-10-electric-beta-release.md#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'

const MyComponent = () => {
  const [items, setItems] = useState([])

  useEffect(() => {
    const fetchItems = async () => {
      const response = await fetch('https://api.example.com/v1/items')
      const data = await response.json()

      setItems(data)
    }

    fetchItems()
  }, [])

  return (
    <List items={ items } />
  )
}
```

